Project Description

A visually appealing, responsive Digital Clock application built using React JS. The clock displays the current time in real-time and allows users to toggle between 12-hour (AM/PM) and 24-hour formats, delivering a smooth and interactive experience.


Features

Real-Time Clock: Continuously updates the current time every second using setInterval.
12-Hour and 24-Hour Formats: Users can switch between 12-hour (AM/PM) and 24-hour formats with dedicated buttons.
Dynamic Styling: The clock is displayed in a styled container with background, shadows, and hover effects for visual appeal.
Responsive Layout: The interface adapts smoothly to different screen sizes and maintains readability.
Clean and Interactive UI: Buttons and time display have hover and active effects for better user experience.
Automatic Time Formatting: Hours, minutes, and seconds are padded to always display two digits for consistency.


Implementation

HTML / JSX Structure
The application uses React JSX to render the clock and format toggle buttons. A container holds the time display and buttons, styled dynamically using CSS-in-JS.

Styling
CSS is used to create a visually appealing interface. The container has padding, border-radius, background color, shadow effects, and hover animations. Buttons are styled with hover and active effects, and the background includes a clock image with gradient overlay for better readability.


React State Management
Reactâ€™s useState hook manages the current time (current) and the selected time format (t24). The state updates every second using useEffect with setInterval.

Real-Time Time Update Logic
useEffect sets up an interval that updates the current state every 1000 milliseconds. On component unmount, the interval is cleared to prevent memory leaks.

12-Hour and 24-Hour Format Logic
The application checks the t24 state to determine which format to display. In 12-hour mode, it calculates AM/PM and converts hours appropriately. In 24-hour mode, hours are displayed directly.

User Interaction
Clicking the 12 Hours or 24 Hours button updates the t24 state. This triggers React to re-render the component with the selected format immediately, providing an interactive and responsive experience.


Real-Time UI Updates
The time display updates every second in real-time, and any format changes reflect immediately without page reload. This ensures a smooth and accurate clock experience for the user.